xgecu-gui (0.3.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add File → Preferences… dialog: pick a theme (Light / Dark / Hacker /
    Amber) and set the UI and hex-editor font sizes independently. Changes
    preview live and persist via QSettings; Cancel reverts.
  * New ThemeManager applies a full palette (via the Fusion style) and feeds
    accent colours to the custom-painted widgets, so themes recolour
    everything including the ZIF socket and hex-editor dirty bytes.
  * Rename the "Write buffer to chip…" action to "Write chip…".

 -- Xecaz <xecaz@xecaz.com>  Sat, 30 May 2026 18:00:00 +0200

xgecu-gui (0.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add a generic fuse / config-bit editor (FuseEditorWidget) as a third tab,
    shown when a chip exposes config fuses. Mask-aware hex fields, defaults,
    read / write / verify, with config fuses and lock bits in separate groups
    behind separate confirmation-gated write buttons.
  * Fuse read/write/verify mirror the minipro CLI; present byte-wide fuses as
    8-bit values even on word_size==2 parts (e.g. ATmega328P lfuse 0x62).
  * HexView: copy the current address (right-click or Ctrl+Shift+C) in the
    0x… form the Go-to / Fill / Copy dialogs accept.
  * Verified on real silicon: ATmega328P fuse read and a CKDIV8 write
    round-trip (gated live test).

 -- Xecaz <xecaz@xecaz.com>  Sat, 30 May 2026 12:00:00 +0200

xgecu-gui (0.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian packaging.
  * Bundles minipro infoic.xml / logicic.xml under /usr/share/xgecu-gui/.
  * Installs minipro's udev rules (60-minipro.rules,
    61-minipro-uaccess.rules) so the programmer is usable without root.
  * Ships a .desktop launcher and SVG icon.

 -- Xecaz <xecaz@xecaz.com>  Fri, 29 May 2026 12:00:00 +0200
